  {
    "id": "2034430842702102629",
    "text": "𝗩𝗔𝗡𝗖𝗘 𝗗𝗥𝗢𝗣𝗦 𝗧𝗛𝗘 𝗠𝗜𝗖 𝗢𝗡 𝗔 𝗥𝗘𝗣𝗢𝗥𝗧𝗘𝗥 𝗜𝗡 𝗥𝗘𝗔𝗟 𝗧𝗜𝗠𝗘\n\nA reporter tried to frame voter ID as \"nationalizing elections\" and \"intervening in the democratic process.\"\n\nVance didn't even blink.\n\n𝘐𝘧 𝘸𝘩𝘢𝘵 𝘺𝘰𝘶 𝘮𝘦𝘢𝘯 𝘣𝘺 𝘪𝘯𝘵𝘦𝘳𝘷𝘦𝘯𝘪𝘯𝘨 𝘪𝘯 𝘵𝘩𝘦 𝘦𝘭𝘦𝘤𝘵𝘪𝘰𝘯 𝘪𝘴 𝘵𝘩𝘢𝘵 𝘸𝘦 𝘸𝘢𝘯𝘵 𝘦𝘷𝘦𝘳𝘺𝘣𝘰𝘥𝘺 𝘵𝘰 𝘩𝘢𝘷𝘦 𝘢 𝘷𝘰𝘵𝘦𝘳 𝘐𝘋 𝘣𝘦𝘧𝘰𝘳𝘦 𝘷𝘰𝘵𝘪𝘯𝘨 𝘪𝘯 𝘵𝘩𝘪𝘴 𝘤𝘰𝘶𝘯𝘵𝘳𝘺? 𝘠𝘌𝘚.\n\nThe crowd erupted. And they were right to.\n\nThis is exactly how you handle a loaded question from a reporter trying to poison the framing before the answer begins. You accept the premise on your terms, not theirs. Voter ID isn't \"nationalizing elections.\" It isn't \"voter suppression.\" It isn't an attack on democracy. It is the most basic, common-sense requirement that exists in virtually every democracy on earth. You need ID to buy beer. You need ID to board a plane. You need ID to enter a federal building. Eighty-five percent of white Americans support it. Eighty-two percent of Latino Americans support it. Seventy-six percent of Black Americans support it.\n\nChuck Schumer called all of those people the \"fringe MAGA base.\" Vance just looked a hostile reporter in the eye and said yes — proudly, without apology, to applause.\n\nThat is how you win the argument. Not by explaining yourself defensively. Not by hedging. By owning the position and daring anyone to disagree with the 80% of Americans standing behind you.\n\nThis is why Vance is dangerous to the left. He doesn't take the bait. He resets the trap.",
