    "id": "2034376451881840786",
    "text": "Love how the question is framed: \"nationalizing elections.\" That's obviously not a neutral description. It's a loaded frame designed to make requiring ID to vote sound like federal overreach (i.e., \"voter suppression).\n\nVance does something most Republican politicians never learn to do: he refuses the frame entirely. He doesn't play defense against the implication. He restates the actual policy in plain English and lets the absurdity of the opposition speak for itself.\n\nThis is a skill Republicans need to study.",
